1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:10,658 --> 00:01:11,659
Tell me this isn't true.

3
00:01:14,621 --> 00:01:16,039
DIVORCE SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

4
00:01:16,623 --> 00:01:17,791
Say it.

5
00:01:19,125 --> 00:01:20,126
Deny it.

6
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,338
- Hae-in...
- Say it.

7
00:01:23,963 --> 00:01:25,256
Tell me it's not true.

8
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:29,844
Tell me it wasn't you.

9
00:01:41,314 --> 00:01:42,357
No.

10
00:01:44,692 --> 00:01:46,653
It was me.

11
00:01:50,156 --> 00:01:52,158
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you.

12
00:02:10,468 --> 00:02:11,761
When?

13
00:02:13,555 --> 00:02:14,597
When…

14
00:02:16,850 --> 00:02:18,351
When did you prepare this?

15
00:02:22,355 --> 00:02:23,439
I have…

16
00:02:26,568 --> 00:02:27,777
something to say.

17
00:02:28,903 --> 00:02:29,988
Was it

18
00:02:30,780 --> 00:02:31,865
that day?

19
00:02:33,324 --> 00:02:35,535
The day I told you I was dying?

20
00:02:39,706 --> 00:02:40,832
Yes.

21
00:02:51,426 --> 00:02:52,552
Is that why

22
00:02:53,386 --> 00:02:54,512
you kept

23
00:02:55,763 --> 00:02:57,390
your mouth shut

24
00:02:58,433 --> 00:02:59,934
and didn't tell me?

25
00:03:00,685 --> 00:03:02,437
Because I was going to die soon anyway?

26
00:03:03,688 --> 00:03:04,939
Yes.

27
00:03:19,537 --> 00:03:20,538
So…

28
00:03:24,375 --> 00:03:25,793
you lied all along?

29
00:03:36,054 --> 00:03:37,680
What's wrong?

30
00:03:39,265 --> 00:03:41,142
You've lied through your teeth.

31
00:03:43,937 --> 00:03:45,438
So what's stopping you now?

32
00:03:59,410 --> 00:04:00,870
I found it…

33
00:04:03,539 --> 00:04:04,874
on my way here.

34
00:04:08,253 --> 00:04:09,837
Our lock is still here.

35
00:05:10,732 --> 00:05:11,732
Hae-in.

36
00:05:24,329 --> 00:05:25,913
It's too late to go anywhere.

37
00:05:31,794 --> 00:05:33,338
Stay here. I'll go.

38
00:05:34,505 --> 00:05:35,673
Just…

39
00:05:36,841 --> 00:05:38,176
let me be.

40
00:05:40,136 --> 00:05:41,429
I don't even have

41
00:05:43,181 --> 00:05:44,932
the energy to get mad.

42
00:05:47,435 --> 00:05:48,811
Just hear me out.

43
00:05:50,730 --> 00:05:52,899
I'll tell you why I did that,

44
00:05:53,566 --> 00:05:54,692
what I was feeling,

45
00:05:55,485 --> 00:05:56,694
and what my plan was.

46
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:03,076
No, forget it.

47
00:06:04,744 --> 00:06:05,744
I'm not curious.

48
00:06:47,286 --> 00:06:48,663
I love you, Hong Hae-in.

49
00:06:50,623 --> 00:06:51,623
I love you.

50
00:07:02,009 --> 00:07:03,009
Are you okay?

51
00:08:20,546 --> 00:08:21,839
What are you doing here?

52
00:08:23,007 --> 00:08:25,218
Don't you know you should be more careful?

53
00:08:33,184 --> 00:08:34,184
Let's go inside.

54
00:08:35,811 --> 00:08:37,980
I'll explain everything.

55
00:08:39,690 --> 00:08:40,858
And then,

56
00:08:42,026 --> 00:08:43,110
I'll do as you say.

57
00:08:44,278 --> 00:08:45,696
- So...
- Hyun-woo.

58
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:54,914
If this ever happens again,

59
00:08:59,335 --> 00:09:00,586
don't save me.

60
00:09:42,336 --> 00:09:43,421
I'm so shocked.

61
00:09:43,504 --> 00:09:45,381
Hyun-woo was normal.

62
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,757
What do you mean?

63
00:09:46,841 --> 00:09:49,176
I thought he'd been out of his mind lately

64
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:51,512
since he seemed to truly love Hae-in.

65
00:09:51,596 --> 00:09:54,599
But he was just like any other guy.

66
00:09:54,682 --> 00:09:56,225
I was surprised too.

67
00:09:56,309 --> 00:09:59,061
Who knew he was planning
to divorce her in secret?

68
00:10:02,607 --> 00:10:04,859
- I wonder when it all began.
- What?

69
00:10:06,152 --> 00:10:07,737
Someone must've encouraged him.

70
00:10:07,820 --> 00:10:09,655
I've been suspecting someone too.

71
00:10:09,739 --> 00:10:10,740
Who?

72
00:10:15,578 --> 00:10:16,621
My aunt.

73
00:10:17,455 --> 00:10:18,456
I see.

74
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:21,208
What?

75
00:10:21,292 --> 00:10:24,962
She's been getting in my way
and talking nonsense lately

76
00:10:25,046 --> 00:10:27,381
about Hyun-woo
being more handsome than me.

77
00:10:30,926 --> 00:10:34,013
Recently, it seemed like
those two were sharing a secret.

78
00:10:34,096 --> 00:10:35,473
I saw them last time.

79
00:10:36,807 --> 00:10:38,601
The biggest priority of this business…

80
00:10:41,604 --> 00:10:43,773
- What's going on?
- So why didn't you go?

81
00:10:43,856 --> 00:10:45,066
Why did she go alone?

82
00:10:46,651 --> 00:10:48,819
Why did you let her go alone?

83
00:10:48,903 --> 00:10:50,529
- Send who alone?
- Why?

84
00:10:53,991 --> 00:10:55,618
What? Why is she crying?

85
00:10:56,869 --> 00:11:00,247
They were having a serious talk in secret.

86
00:11:00,831 --> 00:11:01,832
Really?

87
00:11:02,541 --> 00:11:03,834
I wonder what it's about.

88
00:12:17,324 --> 00:12:18,325
Where are you going?

89
00:12:18,409 --> 00:12:20,286
The treatment fell through, so what?

90
00:12:21,078 --> 00:12:23,998
What he means is that we need time.

91
00:12:24,081 --> 00:12:26,751
Let's go back to Korea,
raise your WBC, then return...

92
00:12:26,834 --> 00:12:28,461
You're despicable.

93
00:12:29,378 --> 00:12:34,425
I know you're happy that I'm dying
and have given up everything.

94
00:12:39,013 --> 00:12:41,640
You've given up everything?

95
00:13:15,174 --> 00:13:17,009
So you won't bother trying anymore?

96
00:13:21,555 --> 00:13:22,932
What about a lawsuit?

97
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,602
I'd be grateful if you divorced me

98
00:13:27,603 --> 00:13:28,813
without filing a suit.

99
00:13:32,817 --> 00:13:34,735
- What?
- You know everything now.

100
00:13:35,986 --> 00:13:37,154
So?

101
00:13:37,696 --> 00:13:40,699
You wouldn't let me go that easily.

102
00:13:42,326 --> 00:13:44,662
It was unbearable to live with you anyway.

103
00:13:46,747 --> 00:13:49,124
Don't act like you had no idea, Hae-in.

104
00:13:49,792 --> 00:13:52,211
You know what kind of person you are.

105
00:13:54,630 --> 00:13:56,090
No wonder I chose to do so.

106
00:13:57,716 --> 00:14:00,803
I could've lived
a comfortable and wealthy life,

107
00:14:00,886 --> 00:14:02,888
so why did I want to run away?

108
00:14:07,685 --> 00:14:10,354
Because I hated living with you
more than anything!

109
00:14:14,441 --> 00:14:15,441
Hey.

110
00:14:16,485 --> 00:14:18,737
- Baek Hyun-woo.
- Yes, you're right.

111
00:14:19,405 --> 00:14:20,406
I'll be honest.

112
00:14:21,115 --> 00:14:23,492
When I heard that you'd be dying soon,

113
00:14:24,535 --> 00:14:27,496
I was relieved deep down.

114
00:14:29,415 --> 00:14:31,625
We'd have a clean divorce
if I put up with you

115
00:14:31,709 --> 00:14:33,294
for the next three months.

116
00:14:34,712 --> 00:14:36,171
But I got caught.

117
00:14:38,966 --> 00:14:40,384
Everything's ruined.

118
00:14:45,723 --> 00:14:47,349
So if you choose

119
00:14:48,142 --> 00:14:51,228
not to take any action at all
and just divorce me,

120
00:14:53,314 --> 00:14:54,773
then honestly,

121
00:14:55,941 --> 00:14:56,941
I'd be grateful.

122
00:15:01,071 --> 00:15:02,197
Will you do that?

123
00:15:06,994 --> 00:15:07,995
What should I do?

124
00:15:09,204 --> 00:15:10,998
Should I pack up and leave once we return?

125
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:12,458
Or…

126
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:17,212
If I continue to grovel at your feet,
will you revise your will?

127
00:15:26,513 --> 00:15:28,098
Are you sure you can handle this?

128
00:15:31,226 --> 00:15:34,104
Do you think you can handle my rage?

129
00:15:38,484 --> 00:15:39,902
Then bring it on!

130
00:15:41,946 --> 00:15:43,155
What will you do?

131
00:15:44,156 --> 00:15:45,699
Do something if you can!

132
00:16:16,146 --> 00:16:18,857
Mr. Song has gone through
his first round of interrogations,

133
00:16:18,941 --> 00:16:23,362
but our attorneys doubt
that the prosecution will stop here.

134
00:16:23,445 --> 00:16:25,948
If that's how
the prosecution will proceed,

135
00:16:26,031 --> 00:16:29,118
then it'll only be a matter of time
until they summon you.

136
00:16:29,201 --> 00:16:31,495
Look at this mess we're in
thanks to Hyun-woo.

137
00:16:31,578 --> 00:16:35,040
I'm worried about them summoning you.

138
00:16:35,124 --> 00:16:37,209
You need to take your medications on time.

139
00:16:37,292 --> 00:16:39,211
Then you can go instead.

140
00:16:39,962 --> 00:16:41,046
- Sorry?
- What's wrong?

141
00:16:41,130 --> 00:16:45,759
I was behind bars for ten months
when I was Soo-cheol's age.

142
00:16:47,011 --> 00:16:48,012
Gosh.

143
00:16:48,095 --> 00:16:50,681
If only I was as young as Soo-cheol.

144
00:16:57,146 --> 00:16:58,814
Why are you looking at me?

145
00:17:00,774 --> 00:17:04,361
This is an experience
that you can't even buy with money.

146
00:17:04,445 --> 00:17:05,571
I'm not interested.

147
00:17:05,654 --> 00:17:10,200
If you appear in his stead,
people will think you're the heir.

148
00:17:10,284 --> 00:17:12,286
But if you don't,
they'll think you're terrible.

149
00:17:12,369 --> 00:17:14,204
I have a family to protect.

150
00:17:14,288 --> 00:17:16,081
And so do I.

151
00:17:16,165 --> 00:17:18,042
Yes, that's me. You should protect me.

152
00:17:18,125 --> 00:17:19,543
What are you saying?

153
00:17:19,626 --> 00:17:20,794
Be quiet!

154
00:17:21,795 --> 00:17:25,591
The problem is that we have
an important investment deal coming up.

155
00:17:25,674 --> 00:17:28,927
If the investors find out,
the deal might fall through.

156
00:17:29,011 --> 00:17:31,472
He's right, sir.
We should hasten the deal.

157
00:17:31,555 --> 00:17:34,349
We have a whole feast
prepared in front of us

158
00:17:34,433 --> 00:17:36,018
that could be taken by Chairman Yeom.

159
00:17:36,101 --> 00:17:38,395
The reporters
will find out sooner or later.

160
00:17:38,479 --> 00:17:42,566
Mr. Yoon will opt out immediately then.
And that's what Chairman Yeom wants.

161
00:17:42,649 --> 00:17:45,903
First, we need to secure the deal.

162
00:17:48,030 --> 00:17:49,030
Grandfather!

163
00:18:42,417 --> 00:18:44,294
QUEENS MART ENTERS NEW RESORT BUSINESS

164
00:18:46,338 --> 00:18:48,757
Once the construction begins,

165
00:18:48,841 --> 00:18:52,427
we'll insinuate the licensing issue
related to altitude restrictions

166
00:18:52,511 --> 00:18:54,179
to the investors.

167
00:18:54,263 --> 00:18:56,682
Then the investors and stock firms
who gave out loans

168
00:18:56,765 --> 00:18:59,643
will choose the pre-payment option.

169
00:18:59,726 --> 00:19:02,646
Soo-cheol, that coward, will be shocked.

170
00:19:02,729 --> 00:19:03,814
He might even cry.

171
00:19:04,565 --> 00:19:07,276
That's when I'll offer
to invest the amount

172
00:19:07,359 --> 00:19:10,696
that the investors have pulled out
and suggest convertible bonds.

173
00:19:10,779 --> 00:19:13,657
And this is when
the prosecution will investigate?

174
00:19:13,740 --> 00:19:14,658
Correct.

175
00:19:14,741 --> 00:19:17,661
Once the embezzlement news gets out
and the Hong family goes to jail,

176
00:19:17,744 --> 00:19:21,039
I'll use the convertible bonds
to purchase Queens' stocks.

177
00:19:21,123 --> 00:19:25,502
Then I'll combine that with the 4.9%
that I previously purchased

178
00:19:25,586 --> 00:19:28,213
and become the biggest shareholder.

179
00:19:30,299 --> 00:19:32,593
Everything is panning out.

180
00:19:32,676 --> 00:19:35,179
Even Hyun-woo is out of the picture now.

181
00:19:35,262 --> 00:19:39,433
Who knew we'd find
the divorce papers at this perfect timing?

182
00:19:41,101 --> 00:19:42,352
Did Hyun-woo admit to it?

183
00:19:42,436 --> 00:19:44,062
Did he sign the divorce papers?

184
00:19:44,146 --> 00:19:46,690
Why bother asking? Of course, it was him.

185
00:19:46,773 --> 00:19:48,025
How could he do this?

186
00:19:48,108 --> 00:19:49,776
Why do you even wonder?

187
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:51,570
They should just divorce.

188
00:19:51,653 --> 00:19:55,532
He bugged your room
and gave the tapes to the prosecution.

189
00:19:55,616 --> 00:19:57,367
But I can look past them.

190
00:19:57,451 --> 00:19:58,535
Why would you?

191
00:19:59,119 --> 00:20:02,289
Our family is awfully tolerant
of their parents' sufferings.

192
00:20:02,372 --> 00:20:04,499
One thing I don't understand

193
00:20:04,583 --> 00:20:08,795
is that the scumbag
wanted to divorce her first.

194
00:20:08,879 --> 00:20:10,756
That's the one thing I understand.

195
00:20:11,673 --> 00:20:13,133
I'm sure there's someone.

196
00:20:14,259 --> 00:20:15,636
Perhaps, a mistress.

197
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:18,555
- Father, I'll look into it.
- No.

198
00:20:19,723 --> 00:20:21,433
- The Audit Team will.
- They will?

199
00:20:21,516 --> 00:20:24,853
He'll leave Queens after the divorce.
I need to find out before then.

200
00:20:24,937 --> 00:20:28,607
I'll look through his computer,
financial documents, phone, and account.

201
00:20:28,690 --> 00:20:29,858
I'll track his funds.

202
00:20:29,942 --> 00:20:33,028
I'll find out whom he met
and what he's been up to.

203
00:20:33,111 --> 00:20:35,948
The moment I find
any embezzlement or illegal act,

204
00:20:36,031 --> 00:20:39,243
I will report him
and file a claim for damages.

205
00:20:41,328 --> 00:20:43,580
- You'll go that far?
- Yes, I will.

206
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:51,004
I'll take care of it,
so please don't get in the way.

207
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:02,724
She sure is merciless.

208
00:21:04,434 --> 00:21:06,311
I said I'd pick you up at the airport.

209
00:21:06,395 --> 00:21:07,312
Are you okay?

210
00:21:07,396 --> 00:21:09,564
Hey, are you hurt?

211
00:21:09,648 --> 00:21:11,692
Can you hear me?

212
00:21:11,775 --> 00:21:16,113
Your eardrums can pop when you get beaten.
It happens to many of my clients.

213
00:21:16,905 --> 00:21:17,906
Can you hear me?

214
00:21:18,407 --> 00:21:19,491
That's enough.

215
00:21:19,574 --> 00:21:22,160
So you're okay. You're fine.

216
00:21:22,244 --> 00:21:24,162
Gosh. Well done.

217
00:21:24,955 --> 00:21:26,915
Come here. Let me give you a hug.

218
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:36,133
You should've feigned innocence
since you were acting anyway.

219
00:21:36,216 --> 00:21:37,718
"The divorce papers are nothing.

220
00:21:37,801 --> 00:21:40,012
I was just practicing
to become a divorce attorney."

221
00:21:40,095 --> 00:21:42,431
Couldn't you have improvised?

222
00:21:42,514 --> 00:21:45,851
She must be livid.
I bet she's even more terrifying now.

223
00:21:45,934 --> 00:21:48,228
I bet you're dispirited.

224
00:21:48,312 --> 00:21:49,438
AVAILABLE FOR MONTHLY RENT

225
00:21:49,521 --> 00:21:51,732
You worked so hard
pretending to be in love.

226
00:21:51,815 --> 00:21:53,191
You must feel hopeless now.

227
00:21:53,859 --> 00:21:55,027
You're wrong.

228
00:21:55,110 --> 00:21:56,820
- What do you mean?
- She wasn't mad.

229
00:21:56,903 --> 00:21:58,071
- No?
- No.

230
00:21:59,364 --> 00:22:01,533
And I don't feel hopeless.

231
00:22:03,827 --> 00:22:04,995
- I'm upset.
- Hey.

232
00:22:05,078 --> 00:22:06,788
You're in no position to feel that way.

233
00:22:06,872 --> 00:22:08,081
Hae-in cried.

234
00:22:08,623 --> 00:22:09,708
She did.

235
00:22:10,459 --> 00:22:12,169
And it drove me insane

236
00:22:12,794 --> 00:22:15,589
seeing her crying.

237
00:22:17,341 --> 00:22:18,925
What in the world…

238
00:22:21,136 --> 00:22:22,888
did I do to her?

239
00:22:28,310 --> 00:22:29,144
What's with him?

240
00:22:29,227 --> 00:22:32,314
I thought he couldn't stand
being next to her.

241
00:22:32,397 --> 00:22:34,566
Does he have feelings for her or what?

242
00:22:36,068 --> 00:22:37,903
So what's your next move?

243
00:22:37,986 --> 00:22:39,696
- What move?
- Do you have no plan?

244
00:22:40,322 --> 00:22:42,574
She's probably planning something.

245
00:22:42,657 --> 00:22:44,117
Of course, she is.

246
00:22:44,201 --> 00:22:47,579
You upset her big time,
so I bet she's thinking of the best way

247
00:22:47,662 --> 00:22:48,872
to take revenge.

248
00:22:48,955 --> 00:22:49,955
Exactly.

249
00:22:50,582 --> 00:22:52,084
- She should.
- What do you mean?

250
00:22:52,167 --> 00:22:55,587
She needs that motivation.
She needs to focus on something.

251
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:58,965
So you purposely let her focus
on ruining your life?

252
00:22:59,049 --> 00:23:00,300
Are you a sacrifice?

253
00:23:00,384 --> 00:23:03,261
Are you a soldier
running into a losing battle?

254
00:23:03,345 --> 00:23:04,763
If this ever happens again,

255
00:23:05,889 --> 00:23:06,932
don't save me.

256
00:23:08,475 --> 00:23:10,394
This is the only way she'll live.

257
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:31,039
Hyun-woo.

258
00:23:32,416 --> 00:23:33,458
Why did you do it?

259
00:23:33,542 --> 00:23:36,211
I'm on my way to see your grandfather.
Let's talk later.

260
00:23:36,294 --> 00:23:37,295
It'll be me anyway.

261
00:23:38,964 --> 00:23:40,757
- What do you mean?
- Try all you want.

262
00:23:40,841 --> 00:23:43,009
But the heir will always be me!

263
00:23:46,346 --> 00:23:48,014
Do you still not get it?

264
00:23:48,098 --> 00:23:50,517
Were you that jealous of me
that you'd bug his room?

265
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:53,603
Did you want to know
all the conversations that we were having?

266
00:23:53,687 --> 00:23:55,063
No, I didn't.

267
00:23:55,147 --> 00:23:57,065
- I didn't bug his room.
- I get it.

268
00:23:57,149 --> 00:23:58,358
Get what?

269
00:23:58,859 --> 00:24:01,653
I knew you were up to something
when you put up

270
00:24:01,736 --> 00:24:03,113
with everything Hae-in did.

271
00:24:03,196 --> 00:24:05,490
But what now? You got caught.

272
00:24:09,035 --> 00:24:13,248
I was planning to give you something
once this resort deal became a success.

273
00:24:13,331 --> 00:24:16,042
"I should set up a branch
in Yufuin or Cancún

274
00:24:16,126 --> 00:24:18,336
and send him there.

275
00:24:18,420 --> 00:24:20,505
No, Yufuin is too near.

276
00:24:20,589 --> 00:24:22,757
Hae-in would just need to fly an hour.

277
00:24:22,841 --> 00:24:24,885
He should go to Cancún
if he wants freedom."

278
00:24:24,968 --> 00:24:27,304
That's how much I cared about you.

279
00:24:31,433 --> 00:24:32,267
What?

280
00:24:32,350 --> 00:24:34,352
You need to halt the resort construction.

281
00:24:34,978 --> 00:24:37,439
The consulting firm
that Mr. Yoon introduced

282
00:24:37,522 --> 00:24:41,776
predicted an annual profit of 500 billion,
but the actual figure was 89 billion won.

283
00:24:41,860 --> 00:24:44,196
That's less than 20%. Isn't that odd?

284
00:24:44,279 --> 00:24:47,157
You signed the contract
even before the validity test...

285
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:49,201
You're trying to get in the way again!

286
00:24:49,284 --> 00:24:52,537
Stop worrying about my success.

287
00:24:58,502 --> 00:25:00,587
Don't forget! It'll be me!

288
00:25:08,428 --> 00:25:09,846
I'm sorry for worrying you.

289
00:25:09,930 --> 00:25:11,223
Okay, do explain.

290
00:25:11,306 --> 00:25:13,642
Why did you hide the divorce papers?

291
00:25:13,725 --> 00:25:16,353
Were you going to surprise us
with it later on?

292
00:25:16,436 --> 00:25:19,689
Is that why you've been nitpicking
my words and disobeying me?

293
00:25:19,773 --> 00:25:21,233
Just because of those papers?

294
00:25:23,610 --> 00:25:25,445
Sir, the chairman wants to see you.

295
00:25:25,529 --> 00:25:26,530
Okay.

296
00:25:26,613 --> 00:25:28,448
Please leave all your electronics outside.

297
00:25:28,532 --> 00:25:29,991
Yes, do so.

298
00:25:30,075 --> 00:25:31,701
You could be recording even now.

299
00:25:37,874 --> 00:25:38,875
Come in.

300
00:25:51,763 --> 00:25:53,598
What did Chairman Yeom promise you?

301
00:25:54,266 --> 00:25:55,517
- Sorry?
- The divorce.

302
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:57,769
I couldn't care less about it.

303
00:25:57,852 --> 00:25:59,271
You chose to ruin your luck.

304
00:25:59,896 --> 00:26:00,772
I'm sorry.

305
00:26:00,855 --> 00:26:03,149
But if you bugged my room

306
00:26:03,233 --> 00:26:06,653
and Chairman Yeom handed it over
to the prosecution,

307
00:26:06,736 --> 00:26:08,029
I won't allow that.

308
00:26:08,113 --> 00:26:11,408
Did you scheme
Mr. Song's embezzlement too?

309
00:26:11,491 --> 00:26:13,243
Were you targeting me?

310
00:26:13,326 --> 00:26:16,746
It's true that the embezzlement
was targeted at you.

311
00:26:16,830 --> 00:26:18,415
Are you playing smart with me?

312
00:26:18,498 --> 00:26:21,001
I'm asking if you were behind it!

313
00:26:26,423 --> 00:26:30,051
Director Jo Hyeon-myeong approved
Mr. Song's embezzlement files.

314
00:26:30,135 --> 00:26:32,887
The man next to him has been in charge
of Queens' external audit.

315
00:26:32,971 --> 00:26:35,390
He's Hwang Byeong-u
who has his own accounting firm.

316
00:26:35,473 --> 00:26:37,767
- They went to the same university.
- So what?

317
00:26:38,393 --> 00:26:40,812
He's been doing yearly audits,

318
00:26:40,895 --> 00:26:43,315
so it's odd
that he found no issues until now.

319
00:26:43,398 --> 00:26:44,691
Has his accounting firm

320
00:26:44,774 --> 00:26:47,819
truly been unaware of Mr. Song's
embezzlement for the past five years?

321
00:26:58,872 --> 00:27:03,835
So you're telling me
that Jo Hyeon-myeong schemed with his firm

322
00:27:03,918 --> 00:27:07,255
and turned a blind eye
to the embezzlement?

323
00:27:07,339 --> 00:27:09,174
So that I'd be investigated?

324
00:27:09,257 --> 00:27:10,342
No, sir.

325
00:27:10,425 --> 00:27:13,470
Director Jo didn't do this alone.
Someone ordered him.

326
00:27:14,095 --> 00:27:20,393
I believe that individual bugged your room
and planted the transmitter in mine.

327
00:27:20,477 --> 00:27:22,228
And who is this person?

328
00:27:27,651 --> 00:27:29,110
I haven't found out yet.

329
00:27:29,194 --> 00:27:30,194
What?

330
00:27:30,236 --> 00:27:31,321
You're not even sure,

331
00:27:31,404 --> 00:27:36,201
yet you want me to believe you
after what you did to my granddaughter?

332
00:27:36,284 --> 00:27:37,535
Do you?

333
00:27:37,619 --> 00:27:38,619
Director Jo.

334
00:27:39,746 --> 00:27:41,039
You should hurry.

335
00:27:44,084 --> 00:27:46,878
Why? Because Baek Hyun-woo is after you.

336
00:27:58,348 --> 00:27:59,724
ESTIMATED ASSETS
2,386,690

337
00:28:04,437 --> 00:28:06,106
Are you doing stocks again?

338
00:28:06,189 --> 00:28:07,482
The market is a mess.

339
00:28:07,565 --> 00:28:12,362
It doesn't matter how blue it gets
as long as my baby is red.

340
00:28:13,363 --> 00:28:14,363
QUEENS DEPARTMENT STORE

341
00:28:15,115 --> 00:28:16,825
- It's red.
- What is it?

342
00:28:17,450 --> 00:28:18,450
- Who's your baby?
- No.

343
00:28:18,493 --> 00:28:20,286
- Come on. Tell me.
- No.

344
00:28:20,370 --> 00:28:22,288
No!

345
00:28:22,997 --> 00:28:24,290
Stop that!

346
00:28:24,374 --> 00:28:25,875
Are you crazy?

347
00:28:25,959 --> 00:28:28,002
You bought Queens' stocks?

348
00:28:28,086 --> 00:28:29,963
Mom will kill me, so be quiet!

349
00:28:30,839 --> 00:28:32,382
Why would you buy them?

350
00:28:34,801 --> 00:28:37,303
I had them in the past, but I sold them.

351
00:28:37,387 --> 00:28:40,348
- When?
- When Hyun-woo mentioned the divorce.

352
00:28:40,432 --> 00:28:43,601
I couldn't ignore the owner's risk.

353
00:28:43,685 --> 00:28:47,856
Nothing good would've come out
of the media mentioning their divorce.

354
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,733
How sly of you.

355
00:28:50,358 --> 00:28:53,236
Then you bought them again
when Hyun-woo decided not to divorce?

356
00:28:53,319 --> 00:28:55,238
Right. Check this out.

357
00:28:55,321 --> 00:28:57,115
- It's going up, right?
- Jeez.

358
00:28:59,117 --> 00:29:00,117
Mom.

359
00:29:01,536 --> 00:29:03,496
It's unlike you to take a nap.

360
00:29:03,580 --> 00:29:04,789
I had a bad dream.

361
00:29:05,749 --> 00:29:07,500
- Gosh.
- What was it about?

362
00:29:07,584 --> 00:29:08,710
It was ambiguous.

363
00:29:08,793 --> 00:29:11,254
What was it?
Maybe it was a conception dream.

364
00:29:11,337 --> 00:29:12,213
Hyun-woo's a dad?

365
00:29:12,297 --> 00:29:14,299
It wasn't anything cute like that.

366
00:29:23,850 --> 00:29:25,518
MOM

367
00:29:31,566 --> 00:29:33,067
- Hello?
- Hello?

368
00:29:33,735 --> 00:29:36,112
Isn't this Mr. Baek Hyun-woo's phone?

369
00:29:36,196 --> 00:29:37,572
Yes, it is.

370
00:29:37,655 --> 00:29:39,032
I'm Hae-in's mother.

371
00:29:39,741 --> 00:29:42,202
Hello, Ms. Kim. How have you been?

372
00:29:42,285 --> 00:29:45,789
I guess Hyun-woo left his phone behind.

373
00:29:45,872 --> 00:29:47,624
- But why are you...
- Yes.

374
00:29:48,333 --> 00:29:50,335
He's speaking with my father-in-law.

375
00:29:50,418 --> 00:29:53,046
I don't know if you know,

376
00:29:53,129 --> 00:29:55,673
but Hyun-woo
turned our family upside down.

377
00:29:55,757 --> 00:29:57,091
What? What happened?

378
00:29:57,175 --> 00:29:59,469
My father-in-law's room was bugged…

379
00:30:02,222 --> 00:30:03,681
Forget it.

380
00:30:03,765 --> 00:30:06,142
Did you know Hyun-woo wanted a divorce?

381
00:30:08,061 --> 00:30:11,022
He did mention it before.

382
00:30:11,105 --> 00:30:15,026
But it's normal for a married couple
to go through rough patches.

383
00:30:15,109 --> 00:30:17,529
I thought they had resolved it.

384
00:30:17,612 --> 00:30:19,280
She knows about the divorce.

385
00:30:19,697 --> 00:30:20,740
Look…

386
00:30:21,741 --> 00:30:24,577
You should hear them out first.

387
00:30:24,661 --> 00:30:26,538
You told me not to get in their way

388
00:30:26,621 --> 00:30:28,373
on the day they got married.

389
00:30:28,456 --> 00:30:32,168
But you see,
I will make sure they part ways.

390
00:30:32,252 --> 00:30:33,628
So don't get in my way.

391
00:30:35,839 --> 00:30:37,340
Mom, what did she say?

392
00:30:38,341 --> 00:30:39,425
What do I do?

393
00:30:41,719 --> 00:30:43,805
Goodness. What do I do?

394
00:30:44,556 --> 00:30:45,598
Unbelievable.

395
00:30:48,017 --> 00:30:49,310
Mom.

396
00:30:54,023 --> 00:30:55,358
It must be a mess.

397
00:30:55,900 --> 00:30:57,986
What if he really gets a divorce?

398
00:31:05,326 --> 00:31:06,326
You bastard.

399
00:31:06,703 --> 00:31:08,329
SELL

400
00:31:08,413 --> 00:31:09,539
YOUR ORDER IS COMPLETE

401
00:31:11,249 --> 00:31:12,125
I sold them.

402
00:31:12,208 --> 00:31:14,836
It's nothing complicated.

403
00:31:14,919 --> 00:31:17,672
Just do what they did with the apples.

404
00:31:17,755 --> 00:31:20,341
Ms. Hong can take a bite
of your pear and say,

405
00:31:20,425 --> 00:31:23,469
"Gosh, that's sweet."
That's all she needs to do.

406
00:31:23,553 --> 00:31:24,971
I should ask her for help again?

407
00:31:25,054 --> 00:31:27,056
She was supposed to help us.

408
00:31:27,140 --> 00:31:29,434
They're the ones who took advantage of it.

409
00:31:30,393 --> 00:31:32,020
What's your take on this?

410
00:31:32,103 --> 00:31:33,855
It's already incredible

411
00:31:33,938 --> 00:31:36,816
that she made time
to come down here and flex.

412
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:39,319
And you want to ask her for help again?

413
00:31:40,028 --> 00:31:41,404
It won't be easy.

414
00:31:42,196 --> 00:31:43,740
- Exactly.
- You'll lose face.

415
00:31:43,823 --> 00:31:45,283
Right?

416
00:31:45,366 --> 00:31:48,745
Then will you let
Park Seok-hun take everything?

417
00:31:48,828 --> 00:31:52,165
You're always so extreme.

418
00:31:52,248 --> 00:31:53,708
Are you an INFP?

419
00:31:55,543 --> 00:31:57,712
What do you mean? I'm Park Chun-sik.

420
00:31:57,795 --> 00:32:00,798
I'm talking about your goals.
Will you do anything to reach them?

421
00:32:00,882 --> 00:32:02,508
Or does the process matter more?

422
00:32:02,592 --> 00:32:04,886
INFP or ENFJ.

423
00:32:09,057 --> 00:32:10,808
In that case…

424
00:32:11,684 --> 00:32:12,685
I'm an INFP.

425
00:32:13,311 --> 00:32:16,189
Then feed her some pears
and tell her to comment on it.

426
00:32:16,272 --> 00:32:18,608
First, we need to remove
the video of her eating the apple.

427
00:32:18,691 --> 00:32:20,777
If you don't want enemies
stealing your food,

428
00:32:20,860 --> 00:32:24,113
- don't set the table in front of them.
- That does make sense.

429
00:32:25,573 --> 00:32:27,408
Dad, why haven't you been picking up?

430
00:32:27,492 --> 00:32:30,244
It's out of battery. I'm glad you're here.

431
00:32:30,328 --> 00:32:32,914
Take down that video of Hae-in
eating the apple.

432
00:32:32,997 --> 00:32:34,040
I already have.

433
00:32:34,123 --> 00:32:36,334
That's not the issue. I have bad news.

434
00:32:36,417 --> 00:32:37,418
What is it?

435
00:32:39,712 --> 00:32:40,713
Gosh.

436
00:32:41,506 --> 00:32:43,967
You'll all find out eventually.

437
00:32:46,928 --> 00:32:48,304
Hyun-woo…

438
00:32:49,430 --> 00:32:52,266
Goodness. What do we do?

439
00:32:52,350 --> 00:32:53,685
They're getting a divorce?

440
00:32:53,768 --> 00:32:56,020
Hyeon-tae, do you have any anxiety pills?

441
00:32:56,104 --> 00:32:58,856
- Of course not.
- That's not the problem.

442
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:00,483
He should overcome it.

443
00:33:00,566 --> 00:33:02,318
Damn it!

444
00:33:04,487 --> 00:33:06,072
Is this entertaining for you?

445
00:33:06,155 --> 00:33:10,243
You see, I'd like to use Dr. Oh's solution
in this situation.

446
00:33:10,326 --> 00:33:12,829
It was Episode 58,
the one with Nancy Lang.

447
00:33:12,912 --> 00:33:15,957
Dr. Oh mentioned three steps
to overcome hardships in life.

448
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:18,001
- I saw it but forgot.
- Step one.

449
00:33:18,084 --> 00:33:18,960
Acknowledgement.

450
00:33:19,043 --> 00:33:22,380
Accurately assess the current crisis.

451
00:33:23,715 --> 00:33:25,550
Did they hand in the divorce papers?

452
00:33:26,509 --> 00:33:27,509
I don't think so.

453
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:30,263
Step two. Self-awareness.

454
00:33:30,346 --> 00:33:34,892
Find out how bad the situation is
and how much worse it could get.

455
00:33:35,685 --> 00:33:37,437
Were there any articles or tabloids?

456
00:33:37,979 --> 00:33:40,690
Not yet. But it'll only be
a matter of time, right?

457
00:33:40,773 --> 00:33:41,774
Of course.

458
00:33:42,775 --> 00:33:44,777
And lastly, sorting it out.

459
00:33:44,861 --> 00:33:48,239
Decide what you'll give up on
and what you'll keep. Then act on it.

460
00:33:52,076 --> 00:33:54,245
Who cares about the election anymore?

461
00:33:54,328 --> 00:33:55,455
Forget it.

462
00:33:56,956 --> 00:33:59,500
- Where are you going?
- Where's your mom?

463
00:33:59,584 --> 00:34:02,003
She just left.
I don't know where she went.

464
00:34:02,086 --> 00:34:05,965
Did you have to mention
the election right now?

465
00:34:06,049 --> 00:34:07,050
Sorry.

466
00:34:07,133 --> 00:34:08,384
I'm an INTP.

467
00:34:10,845 --> 00:34:14,557
YONGDU-RI SUPERMARKET

468
00:34:14,640 --> 00:34:17,643
What is he talking about?

469
00:34:17,727 --> 00:34:21,147
Hyun-woo's mom knew everything
and lied to us.

470
00:34:21,230 --> 00:34:24,317
How dare they upload that video
of Hae-in when she knew nothing?

471
00:34:25,068 --> 00:34:26,110
Calm down.

472
00:34:26,194 --> 00:34:27,904
Be calm as her mom.

473
00:34:27,987 --> 00:34:29,614
Imagine how Hae-in must feel.

474
00:34:30,907 --> 00:34:32,033
Seon-hwa!

475
00:34:32,533 --> 00:34:33,534
What's going on?

476
00:34:33,618 --> 00:34:35,078
Did Hyun-woo really do that?

477
00:34:35,161 --> 00:34:37,663
You were always defending him.

478
00:34:37,747 --> 00:34:39,082
What did I tell you?

479
00:34:39,165 --> 00:34:43,336
You're such a poor judge of character.
No wonder you're always betrayed.

480
00:34:44,212 --> 00:34:45,505
Don't blame me.

481
00:34:48,049 --> 00:34:51,135
You'll always be duped
if someone is determined to trick you.

482
00:34:52,804 --> 00:34:54,514
Why shouldn't I tell anyone?

483
00:34:54,597 --> 00:34:56,641
That bitch has been deceiving us
for over 20 years!

484
00:34:56,724 --> 00:34:57,724
Exactly.

485
00:34:57,767 --> 00:35:00,478
That just proves how savage she is.

486
00:35:00,561 --> 00:35:02,522
If you don't have proof,

487
00:35:02,605 --> 00:35:04,982
she'll just deny it
and turn you into a fool.

488
00:35:05,066 --> 00:35:08,945
Let's be patient. She has a son,
so she must be sending him money.

489
00:35:09,028 --> 00:35:10,238
Let's find him first.

490
00:35:10,321 --> 00:35:12,782
In the meantime,
keep your temper under control.

491
00:35:13,491 --> 00:35:14,659
You must.

492
00:35:20,373 --> 00:35:24,001
I wouldn't be able to relate
since I'm not a mom.

493
00:35:24,085 --> 00:35:27,672
But then again,
I guess the same goes for you.

494
00:35:31,092 --> 00:35:33,010
You don't need to be a mom to relate.

495
00:35:33,761 --> 00:35:35,596
I can imagine how she must feel.

496
00:35:35,680 --> 00:35:38,266
Still, think twice about the divorce.

497
00:35:38,349 --> 00:35:39,475
I know times have changed,

498
00:35:39,559 --> 00:35:42,812
but Hae-in will suffer
more than him if they divorce.

499
00:35:42,895 --> 00:35:44,147
Take her for example.

500
00:35:46,983 --> 00:35:48,067
Why are you looking at me?

501
00:35:48,151 --> 00:35:51,154
Unlike her ex-husbands
who have all happily remarried,

502
00:35:51,237 --> 00:35:52,822
Beom-ja is still single.

503
00:35:52,905 --> 00:35:54,073
What do you mean?

504
00:35:54,157 --> 00:35:56,117
I remarried right away too.

505
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:58,035
And you divorced just as quickly.

506
00:36:00,288 --> 00:36:03,166
Seon-hwa, that's not
the problem right now.

507
00:36:03,249 --> 00:36:04,917
Where's Hae-in? What's she doing?

508
00:36:05,001 --> 00:36:08,212
Gosh, she's already struggling as is.

509
00:36:09,505 --> 00:36:13,009
She's already struggling?
Is something going on with her?

510
00:36:14,010 --> 00:36:15,052
No.

511
00:36:15,136 --> 00:36:18,139
She's just a workaholic.

512
00:36:20,016 --> 00:36:22,059
She needs to take a breather. Damn it.

513
00:36:22,143 --> 00:36:23,143
Jeez.

514
00:36:24,145 --> 00:36:25,688
What is she saying?

515
00:37:14,654 --> 00:37:16,656
There. I signed it too.

516
00:37:17,323 --> 00:37:21,035
But it's up to me
when I'll submit it and how.

517
00:37:22,703 --> 00:37:23,955
Okay.

518
00:37:25,331 --> 00:37:26,958
I can finally understand why

519
00:37:27,041 --> 00:37:29,627
my aunt beat her ex-husbands
to a pulp before the divorce.

520
00:37:29,710 --> 00:37:32,964
I'll hire much more competent attorneys
than she did.

521
00:37:33,923 --> 00:37:35,466
You won't leave this house unscathed.

522
00:37:35,549 --> 00:37:37,510
You will be kicked out mercilessly.

523
00:37:39,387 --> 00:37:40,471
Okay.

524
00:37:42,139 --> 00:37:43,224
I get it.

525
00:37:52,441 --> 00:37:55,027
But please keep your distance
from Yoon Eun-sung.

526
00:37:58,364 --> 00:37:59,240
What's it to you?

527
00:37:59,323 --> 00:38:02,576
He was out of touch for a long time
then suddenly appeared.

528
00:38:02,660 --> 00:38:05,705
Then he gifted Soo-cheol and you
a hefty investment

529
00:38:05,788 --> 00:38:07,206
and the Hercyna deal.

530
00:38:07,790 --> 00:38:09,000
He must have a motive.

531
00:38:09,083 --> 00:38:11,043
- He's suspicious too.
- How so?

532
00:38:14,005 --> 00:38:17,133
There was dashcam footage
of the hunting ground incident.

533
00:38:17,216 --> 00:38:19,760
I gave the SD card
to a data restoring company.

534
00:38:19,844 --> 00:38:22,555
Mr. Yoon visited them,
and the owner has disappeared.

535
00:38:26,892 --> 00:38:30,771
So? How does that prove anything?

536
00:38:30,855 --> 00:38:33,482
He could've simply been another client.

537
00:38:33,566 --> 00:38:35,985
And even if he has
something up his sleeve,

538
00:38:36,068 --> 00:38:37,987
he won't fool me that easily.

539
00:38:38,070 --> 00:38:39,070
But I did.

540
00:38:46,162 --> 00:38:47,830
Just don't make the same mistake.

541
00:39:12,563 --> 00:39:15,441
We've prepared pine mushroom porridge
for breakfast.

542
00:39:15,524 --> 00:39:16,817
- Would you like some?
- No.

543
00:39:17,818 --> 00:39:18,818
I want beef.

544
00:40:21,215 --> 00:40:23,801
Ms. Hong's diamond necklace blinded me.

545
00:40:25,010 --> 00:40:27,471
We have a peacock at large.

546
00:40:27,555 --> 00:40:29,098
- Brace yourselves.
- Yes, ma'am.

547
00:40:30,141 --> 00:40:31,892
I'm sorry, but what peacock?

548
00:40:31,976 --> 00:40:34,311
Right. You're a newbie here.

549
00:40:34,395 --> 00:40:35,771
How did Ms. Hong look?

550
00:40:35,855 --> 00:40:36,772
Gorgeous.

551
00:40:36,856 --> 00:40:37,857
That's true.

552
00:40:40,109 --> 00:40:42,069
Okay, just remember this.

553
00:40:42,153 --> 00:40:44,280
The more upset she is,
the fancier she dresses.

554
00:40:44,363 --> 00:40:47,741
She looked like a fabulous peacock today.

555
00:40:47,825 --> 00:40:49,410
It means we're all dead meat.

556
00:40:50,077 --> 00:40:51,579
Then what should we do?

557
00:40:51,662 --> 00:40:52,830
There's…

558
00:40:53,330 --> 00:40:54,330
no solution.

559
00:40:54,790 --> 00:40:59,503
Natural disasters and Ms. Hong's moodiness
are two things humans can't control.

560
00:41:06,218 --> 00:41:08,721
Gosh, I'm sorry!

561
00:41:08,804 --> 00:41:10,598
I'll reprint these documents and...

562
00:41:10,681 --> 00:41:12,016
It's okay.

563
00:41:13,559 --> 00:41:14,560
Sorry?

564
00:41:14,643 --> 00:41:15,519
What did you…

565
00:41:15,603 --> 00:41:18,147
It's okay.
It's not a life-or-death situation.

566
00:41:18,230 --> 00:41:20,191
Don't feel so bad about spilling.

567
00:41:20,274 --> 00:41:22,234
It's okay. You may go.

568
00:41:23,652 --> 00:41:26,155
Ms. Hong, are you very upset?

569
00:41:27,531 --> 00:41:31,494
No, I have something
that enrages me much more.

570
00:41:32,203 --> 00:41:33,412
This is nothing.

571
00:41:34,246 --> 00:41:35,331
Look.

572
00:41:35,414 --> 00:41:39,835
Even this sloppy report

573
00:41:41,295 --> 00:41:42,713
doesn't enrage me.

574
00:41:46,967 --> 00:41:49,011
She was so terrifying even when not mad.

575
00:41:49,094 --> 00:41:51,430
I wonder what she's enraged about.

576
00:41:54,558 --> 00:41:56,185
We're from the Audit Team.

577
00:41:56,852 --> 00:41:58,646
We're conducting an investigation

578
00:41:58,729 --> 00:42:01,482
after receiving a report
on the illegal use of expenses.

579
00:42:02,775 --> 00:42:03,943
Please stand up.

580
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:06,737
Do not shred any documents.

581
00:42:08,197 --> 00:42:09,865
Do not destroy or move anything.

582
00:42:23,003 --> 00:42:25,589
Gosh, this is total bloodshed.

583
00:42:25,673 --> 00:42:27,883
Has the Hong-Baek Battle begun once again?

584
00:42:27,967 --> 00:42:29,218
This will be a disaster.

585
00:42:29,301 --> 00:42:30,678
Let's go.

586
00:42:38,852 --> 00:42:41,063
- All of them?
- Yes.

587
00:42:41,146 --> 00:42:42,731
- You're going to reject them?
- Yes.

588
00:42:42,815 --> 00:42:45,442
But you already confirmed them
before going to Germany.

589
00:42:45,526 --> 00:42:46,652
I know.

590
00:42:48,195 --> 00:42:49,697
- All of them?
- Yes.

591
00:42:49,780 --> 00:42:51,448
She rejected them all.

592
00:42:51,532 --> 00:42:53,492
It usually lasts a week.

593
00:42:53,576 --> 00:42:55,828
The duration isn't the problem
this time around.

594
00:42:56,370 --> 00:42:57,955
The intensity is on another level.

595
00:42:58,706 --> 00:43:00,791
What in the world happened in Germany?

596
00:43:00,874 --> 00:43:02,793
Let's share their schedules.

597
00:43:02,876 --> 00:43:04,295
Don't let them run into each other.

598
00:43:05,546 --> 00:43:08,465
What? The lunch meeting.
We're having sushi at J Hotel too.

599
00:43:08,549 --> 00:43:11,260
Change it. I'll follow
your schedule for the elevator rides.

600
00:43:11,635 --> 00:43:12,635
Okay.

601
00:43:12,886 --> 00:43:15,431
BAEK HYUN-WOO

602
00:43:23,397 --> 00:43:25,024
QUEENS DEPARTMENT STORE INC.

603
00:43:25,107 --> 00:43:28,152
"We have already reviewed the contracts
for the soon-to-be-closed stores,

604
00:43:28,235 --> 00:43:29,069
so you can proceed.

605
00:43:29,153 --> 00:43:31,989
We have already discussed this,
so you cannot change it.

606
00:43:32,072 --> 00:43:34,992
You'll have to pay triple
the penalty fee if you do.

607
00:43:35,075 --> 00:43:36,660
Please approve it so we can proceed.

608
00:43:36,744 --> 00:43:38,037
Goodbye then."

609
00:43:40,372 --> 00:43:41,624
That's what he said.

610
00:43:44,084 --> 00:43:47,630
"The Legal Team can take care
of penalty issues. I can't approve this.

611
00:43:47,713 --> 00:43:49,632
Shouldn't you have come up

612
00:43:49,715 --> 00:43:52,468
with different scenarios
regarding the possible issues,

613
00:43:52,551 --> 00:43:54,970
run simulations,
and then reported them to me? Again."

614
00:43:56,180 --> 00:43:57,473
That's what she said.

615
00:43:59,141 --> 00:44:01,101
- How feisty.
- Sorry?

616
00:44:02,770 --> 00:44:03,770
Never mind.

617
00:44:04,647 --> 00:44:07,232
Aren't we having sushi at J Hotel today?

618
00:44:07,316 --> 00:44:08,400
Let's go.

619
00:44:10,486 --> 00:44:12,363
How about the Chinese restaurant instead?

620
00:44:13,447 --> 00:44:14,657
Why?

621
00:44:15,074 --> 00:44:17,785
It'd cost a lot for all of us
to have sushi omakase.

622
00:44:17,868 --> 00:44:20,788
It's okay. It's my treat.

623
00:44:21,955 --> 00:44:23,791
I know how hard you've been working.

624
00:44:26,085 --> 00:44:28,212
Let's just have Chinese, sir.

625
00:44:28,295 --> 00:44:31,173
Their sweet
and sour pork lunch set is delicious.

626
00:44:31,256 --> 00:44:32,633
Why all of a sudden?

627
00:44:32,716 --> 00:44:34,635
Is there another reason?

628
00:44:34,718 --> 00:44:36,345
No, not at all.

629
00:44:37,012 --> 00:44:39,139
They all prefer to have Chinese instead.

630
00:44:44,687 --> 00:44:46,063
What's with Mr. Kim's face?

631
00:44:46,146 --> 00:44:48,190
He's going to kill us if we choose sushi.

632
00:44:48,273 --> 00:44:51,193
I bet it's because Ms. Hong
is going there.

633
00:44:51,276 --> 00:44:53,987
I think Mr. Baek caught onto it.
I thought he loved jajangmyeon.

634
00:44:54,071 --> 00:44:55,197
This is entertaining.

635
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:58,367
I don't care what we have.
I just want to watch the rich argue.

636
00:44:58,450 --> 00:44:59,450
ME TOO
ME TOO

637
00:45:02,413 --> 00:45:04,164
The Owl has switched to Chinese.

638
00:45:04,248 --> 00:45:07,292
Okay. The Eagle is headed
to the elevator in Building A.

639
00:45:09,628 --> 00:45:11,505
The Owl is headed to Building B.

640
00:45:16,927 --> 00:45:19,012
It's running late. Let's go to Building B.

641
00:45:20,055 --> 00:45:21,849
But it'll be here soon.

642
00:45:23,016 --> 00:45:25,936
The Eagle has changed course.
Approaching Building B in three minutes.

643
00:45:30,107 --> 00:45:31,400
Should we walk instead?

644
00:45:32,192 --> 00:45:35,154
- It's very healthy to take the stairs.
- Not if you're going down.

645
00:45:41,160 --> 00:45:42,077
Emergency.

646
00:45:42,161 --> 00:45:44,663
Ms. Hong is coming this way! Help!

647
00:45:55,340 --> 00:45:56,967
I'm in the chatroom too.

648
00:45:59,470 --> 00:46:00,679
I'm sorry.

649
00:46:11,315 --> 00:46:13,567
You guys must be eating out together.

650
00:46:13,650 --> 00:46:15,527
You must not have much to do.

651
00:46:15,611 --> 00:46:18,155
I'm treating them
since they have a lot of work.

652
00:46:18,238 --> 00:46:19,406
Sure.

653
00:46:19,490 --> 00:46:20,949
You should do better.

654
00:46:21,033 --> 00:46:23,535
And while you're at it,
give me an analysis report

655
00:46:23,619 --> 00:46:25,120
on the cases you've repeatedly lost

656
00:46:25,204 --> 00:46:28,165
in the past three years
and find out how to improve.

657
00:46:29,333 --> 00:46:30,667
Yes, ma'am.

658
00:46:30,751 --> 00:46:32,377
But when you review it,

659
00:46:33,045 --> 00:46:36,465
I hope you leave out
any personal feelings you have.

660
00:46:36,548 --> 00:46:37,883
I guess you didn't know.

661
00:46:37,966 --> 00:46:39,301
I'm pretty much an AI

662
00:46:39,384 --> 00:46:41,845
when it comes to work,
so don't worry about that.

663
00:46:41,929 --> 00:46:43,555
Is that so? I didn't know.

664
00:46:43,639 --> 00:46:44,932
That ignorance of yours

665
00:46:45,015 --> 00:46:47,726
is the reason
why you keep losing those cases.

666
00:47:15,754 --> 00:47:17,589
Should we take the stairs?

667
00:47:17,673 --> 00:47:18,924
- Sure.
- Let's go.

668
00:47:28,475 --> 00:47:29,518
Did you read the news?

669
00:47:29,601 --> 00:47:31,353
NSFA's new biotechnology was fabricated?

670
00:47:31,436 --> 00:47:34,731
- We invested in them.
- Did you use your shares as collateral?

671
00:47:34,815 --> 00:47:37,359
It was impossible
to get the money in cash.

672
00:47:37,442 --> 00:47:40,362
I even signed
a foreclosure agreement with the bank.

673
00:47:40,445 --> 00:47:42,197
Me too.

674
00:47:42,281 --> 00:47:45,993
What if the bank confiscates our shares?

675
00:47:47,160 --> 00:47:48,453
Can you reach Director Jo?

676
00:47:49,621 --> 00:47:53,125
Gosh, it's sad to see you leave.

677
00:47:53,208 --> 00:47:56,420
- People grow on me so easily.
- Stay healthy.

678
00:47:56,503 --> 00:47:58,171
Your kids will be happy to see you.

679
00:47:58,255 --> 00:48:00,465
Even more so since you're rich now.

680
00:48:00,549 --> 00:48:04,011
I'm starting afresh,
so I'm going to do many good deeds

681
00:48:04,094 --> 00:48:05,094
and help others.

682
00:48:06,597 --> 00:48:07,598
Sure.

683
00:48:08,974 --> 00:48:10,392
The statute of limitations

684
00:48:10,475 --> 00:48:13,395
for financial fraud
of 100 million or more is 25 years.

685
00:48:13,478 --> 00:48:16,064
You can't help others if you're in prison.

686
00:48:16,148 --> 00:48:17,608
So don't get caught.

687
00:48:18,775 --> 00:48:22,446
You bet. I'll stay far away
from Korean marts and restaurants.

688
00:48:22,529 --> 00:48:23,697
I'll live well.

689
00:48:25,741 --> 00:48:26,741
Goodbye then.

690
00:48:29,745 --> 00:48:31,038
What a filthy scumbag.

691
00:48:31,747 --> 00:48:35,542
How is he so brazen after sucking
his long-time colleagues dry?

692
00:48:38,128 --> 00:48:40,088
Goodbye. Go on.

693
00:48:43,717 --> 00:48:45,427
What a dirt bag.

694
00:49:02,736 --> 00:49:04,863
SUNGMIN UNIVERSITY MEDICAL CENTER

695
00:49:15,832 --> 00:49:16,959
BAEK HYUN-WOO

696
00:49:28,553 --> 00:49:29,596
Hae-in.

697
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:47,990
Contact Sungmin Medical Center.
I need to check something.

698
00:49:51,576 --> 00:49:53,578
Goodness, Mr. Baek.

699
00:49:53,662 --> 00:49:55,706
How have you been? What brings you here?

700
00:49:55,789 --> 00:49:57,624
I had a question.

701
00:49:58,208 --> 00:50:00,252
Do you recognize this watch?

702
00:50:00,335 --> 00:50:01,420
I see.

703
00:50:02,087 --> 00:50:05,298
It's a limited edition
for Ronde de Frédic's 101st anniversary.

704
00:50:05,382 --> 00:50:07,092
- Only 101 of them were made.
- I see.

705
00:50:07,759 --> 00:50:09,970
But this one is preordered.

706
00:50:10,053 --> 00:50:11,638
Do you see this yellow diamond?

707
00:50:11,722 --> 00:50:15,892
This diamond was only added to the dials
of the ten preordered watches.

708
00:50:17,602 --> 00:50:18,979
I know it's a lot to ask,

709
00:50:19,062 --> 00:50:21,732
but may I know
who bought those ten watches?

710
00:50:22,607 --> 00:50:23,942
Sure, I can help you.

711
00:50:24,026 --> 00:50:27,946
You helped my mom resolve
the medical malpractice incident.

712
00:50:28,572 --> 00:50:30,574
I'm close with HQ's team leader.

713
00:50:30,657 --> 00:50:31,950
Don't worry.

714
00:50:32,034 --> 00:50:32,909
Thank you.

715
00:50:32,993 --> 00:50:34,578
I'll turn now.

716
00:50:34,661 --> 00:50:35,746
Look far ahead.

717
00:50:35,829 --> 00:50:36,913
- Slowly.
- Good.

718
00:50:37,831 --> 00:50:38,915
Straighten your back.

719
00:50:38,999 --> 00:50:40,459
Step on the pedal. That's it.

720
00:50:40,542 --> 00:50:43,378
Good, turn. Yes, slowly.

721
00:50:43,462 --> 00:50:46,298
Slowly. That was good.

722
00:50:46,381 --> 00:50:47,381
Turn smoothly.

723
00:50:47,424 --> 00:50:49,092
- Like this?
- Yes, that's right.

724
00:50:49,176 --> 00:50:51,386
- You're doing great.
- Okay.

725
00:50:54,264 --> 00:50:56,433
You're terrific.
Are you really a beginner?

726
00:50:56,516 --> 00:50:59,728
I don't need these extra wheels,
but he kept insisting.

727
00:51:00,687 --> 00:51:02,606
You know him, right?
He's a bronze medalist.

728
00:51:02,689 --> 00:51:04,983
- Yes.
- I should listen to the pro.

729
00:51:05,067 --> 00:51:06,943
Everyone uses
the training wheels at first.

730
00:51:07,027 --> 00:51:09,488
I'd be flying without them.

731
00:51:10,030 --> 00:51:11,281
Watch me.

732
00:51:12,699 --> 00:51:15,035
- I'll go faster.
- Okay, but relax.

733
00:51:15,118 --> 00:51:16,912
Slowly. That's it.

734
00:51:16,995 --> 00:51:18,455
- Like this?
- That's right.

735
00:51:18,538 --> 00:51:20,082
Go in a straight line.

736
00:51:22,375 --> 00:51:23,710
Are you okay?

737
00:51:23,794 --> 00:51:26,296
Goodness, my son! Soo-cheol!

738
00:51:26,379 --> 00:51:28,215
Oh, dear!

739
00:51:29,132 --> 00:51:30,217
You're bleeding!

740
00:51:30,300 --> 00:51:32,803
Why didn't you guys stop him?

741
00:51:32,886 --> 00:51:34,304
Why would they need to?

742
00:51:34,387 --> 00:51:38,642
Can't you see all this dirt and cement?
Why would you ride here? It's dangerous.

743
00:51:38,725 --> 00:51:41,228
- Don't ride this.
- Come on, Mom!

744
00:51:44,147 --> 00:51:48,110
Skateboards, bicycles,
skis, rollerblades, and kick scooters.

745
00:51:49,027 --> 00:51:52,072
I can't ride any of them because of you.

746
00:51:52,155 --> 00:51:55,659
You didn't even let me ride steep slides,
so I've had no experience.

747
00:51:55,742 --> 00:51:57,577
Because you might fall...

748
00:51:57,661 --> 00:51:59,204
Exactly. I've never fallen before.

749
00:52:00,539 --> 00:52:01,539
That's right.

750
00:52:01,581 --> 00:52:04,167
Now, do you understand
how much I doted on you?

751
00:52:04,251 --> 00:52:06,253
Why must you fall?

752
00:52:06,336 --> 00:52:07,587
Mom.

753
00:52:07,671 --> 00:52:08,922
As his dad,

754
00:52:09,756 --> 00:52:12,384
I should at least teach Geon-u
how to ride a bicycle.

755
00:52:13,051 --> 00:52:15,470
So it's just to teach
your son how to ride?

756
00:52:15,554 --> 00:52:16,555
- That's why?
- Yes.

757
00:52:16,638 --> 00:52:17,764
I'm going to teach him

758
00:52:18,515 --> 00:52:21,434
how to ride bicycles,
rollerblades, kick scooters,

759
00:52:21,518 --> 00:52:24,604
skateboards, and skis.

760
00:52:25,522 --> 00:52:28,692
You can just hire someone to teach him.

761
00:52:28,775 --> 00:52:31,695
Why would you
put yourself in danger like that?

762
00:52:31,778 --> 00:52:34,406
Dads are supposed
to teach their kids these things.

763
00:52:35,073 --> 00:52:36,073
I'll begin.

764
00:52:37,159 --> 00:52:39,703
- All right.
- No, Soo-cheol. You'll fall.

765
00:52:39,786 --> 00:52:42,873
- Soo-cheol...
- Mr. Kim, move the car!

766
00:52:42,956 --> 00:52:44,457
- Mom, come on.
- Get off.

767
00:52:45,125 --> 00:52:47,335
Move the car, or I'll crash into it.

768
00:52:47,878 --> 00:52:48,878
Hello?

769
00:52:48,920 --> 00:52:51,089
Hello, this is Kevin from Manhattan.

770
00:52:51,173 --> 00:52:52,090
Hello.

771
00:52:52,174 --> 00:52:56,178
It's about the Upper West Side apartment.
The owner wants to sell it.

772
00:53:00,182 --> 00:53:01,433
That's great.

773
00:53:01,516 --> 00:53:05,812
Then I'll proceed. The contract
will be valid until the end of the month.

774
00:53:05,896 --> 00:53:07,898
Will you be here by then?

775
00:53:07,981 --> 00:53:10,692
You need to sign it yourself.

776
00:53:14,696 --> 00:53:16,323
I'll be there in two weeks.

777
00:53:16,948 --> 00:53:19,868
Ma'am, there's something odd
I found out about Mr. Baek.

778
00:53:19,951 --> 00:53:21,244
What is it?

779
00:53:21,328 --> 00:53:24,873
He kept calling a woman's name
on the rooftop garden.

780
00:53:24,956 --> 00:53:25,956
A woman's name?

781
00:53:40,597 --> 00:53:41,890
Yeong-suk.

782
00:53:47,979 --> 00:53:48,979
Yeong-suk?

783
00:53:53,610 --> 00:53:54,610
Yeong...

784
00:54:00,408 --> 00:54:02,619
Come out if you're here.

785
00:54:03,495 --> 00:54:05,080
Her name is Yeong-suk.

786
00:54:06,539 --> 00:54:08,291
Oh, that?

787
00:54:08,375 --> 00:54:10,835
He keeps telling her to come out.

788
00:54:10,919 --> 00:54:12,128
Forget it.

789
00:54:12,754 --> 00:54:14,839
I recognize that name.

790
00:54:16,508 --> 00:54:17,550
Yes, ma'am.

791
00:54:46,913 --> 00:54:48,290
Did you find anything?

792
00:54:48,873 --> 00:54:52,085
We've been keeping a close eye
on Mr. Baek around the clock lately.

793
00:54:52,168 --> 00:54:55,755
This is what he's been doing every hour.

794
00:54:57,882 --> 00:55:00,677
The places he went to weren't typical.

795
00:55:00,760 --> 00:55:02,304
What has he been up to?

796
00:55:04,514 --> 00:55:05,807
What? "Coin baseball"?

797
00:55:05,890 --> 00:55:07,809
Yes, five balls for five hundred won.

798
00:55:07,892 --> 00:55:09,728
He always goes there after work.

799
00:55:09,811 --> 00:55:10,937
- With whom?
- Alone.

800
00:55:18,445 --> 00:55:20,238
Forget it. Next.

801
00:55:20,905 --> 00:55:22,282
What is "Grandma's Home Cooking"?

802
00:55:22,365 --> 00:55:25,076
They sell home-cooked meals.
He has dinner there every day.

803
00:55:25,160 --> 00:55:26,160
- With whom?
- Alone.

804
00:55:32,125 --> 00:55:34,711
I tried their food for research purposes.

805
00:55:34,794 --> 00:55:38,006
It was delicious. I'd go there alone too.

806
00:55:38,089 --> 00:55:40,633
Why would he act pitifully and eat alone?

807
00:55:40,717 --> 00:55:42,344
He can always eat at home.

808
00:55:44,429 --> 00:55:47,140
What about two days ago?
He came home at midnight.

809
00:55:47,223 --> 00:55:49,434
Right. He enjoyed some pork bulgogi

810
00:55:50,060 --> 00:55:52,562
at Grandma's Home Cooking for dinner,

811
00:55:52,645 --> 00:55:54,606
bought two water bottles
at a convenience store,

812
00:55:54,689 --> 00:55:56,733
and went to an elementary school nearby.

813
00:55:56,816 --> 00:55:59,819
At that hour? Was it a secret rendezvous?

814
00:55:59,903 --> 00:56:00,903
No, he was alone.

815
00:56:01,988 --> 00:56:03,990
- What did he do there by himself?
- He ran.

816
00:56:05,325 --> 00:56:06,701
- He ran?
- Yes.

817
00:56:06,785 --> 00:56:10,080
You know teachers punish their students
by making them do laps.

818
00:56:10,163 --> 00:56:12,791
That's what he was doing.

819
00:56:12,874 --> 00:56:14,209
- What for?
- Beats me.

820
00:56:14,292 --> 00:56:19,172
It's not like he's an athlete,
but he even sang and shouted.

821
00:56:19,255 --> 00:56:21,007
I was a bit spooked.

822
00:56:21,091 --> 00:56:22,384
Would you like to see?

823
00:56:32,602 --> 00:56:38,900
Don't ask me why I'm leaving

824
00:56:38,983 --> 00:56:40,735
I was

825
00:56:40,819 --> 00:56:44,364
Such a fool

826
00:56:44,447 --> 00:56:45,740
What's wrong with him?

827
00:56:45,824 --> 00:56:48,034
I told you, sir. He's not typical.

828
00:56:48,910 --> 00:56:51,162
He met up with a stray cat
on his way home.

829
00:56:51,246 --> 00:56:53,456
He said hello and gave it a snack.

830
00:56:53,832 --> 00:56:55,375
I didn't expect a mistress,

831
00:56:55,458 --> 00:56:57,377
but I did expect to see some tycoons.

832
00:56:57,460 --> 00:56:59,087
Did you do your job properly?

833
00:56:59,170 --> 00:57:01,881
I don't want to brag, but you see…

834
00:57:01,965 --> 00:57:05,552
I'm so competent that I can locate
a target even in North Korea.

835
00:57:05,635 --> 00:57:07,846
That's true. He's very tenacious.

836
00:57:08,847 --> 00:57:10,432
As the legal director of Queens,

837
00:57:10,515 --> 00:57:13,393
his only rendezvous was with a cat?

838
00:57:13,476 --> 00:57:14,936
It's Aeong.

839
00:57:15,019 --> 00:57:16,312
- What is?
- The cat's name.

840
00:57:16,938 --> 00:57:19,023
It's the most ferocious cat
in this neighborhood.

841
00:57:19,107 --> 00:57:21,484
But he named it, and it listens to him.

842
00:57:21,568 --> 00:57:25,947
I also hired a former-CSI hacker
to hack his phone.

843
00:57:26,030 --> 00:57:28,158
There were many photos of Aeong.

844
00:57:36,875 --> 00:57:39,752
Strange, right? We thought the same thing.

845
00:57:39,836 --> 00:57:43,882
What kind of man takes such pretty photos
of his woman whom he wants to divorce?

846
00:57:43,965 --> 00:57:48,261
If you look closely,
this photo makes her legs look long.

847
00:57:48,344 --> 00:57:50,930
This photo requires
a lot of concentration.

848
00:57:51,014 --> 00:57:52,599
- This is true love.
- Totally.

849
00:58:03,568 --> 00:58:07,489
I don't think he has a woman on the side.

850
00:58:07,572 --> 00:58:08,990
This doesn't prove anything.

851
00:58:09,741 --> 00:58:12,160
You've put a tail on him many times.

852
00:58:12,243 --> 00:58:15,205
He knows to behave well
at times like this.

853
00:58:15,288 --> 00:58:16,623
Do you think so?

854
00:58:16,706 --> 00:58:18,750
The numbers will tell.

855
00:58:19,834 --> 00:58:21,461
The audit results will come out soon.

856
00:58:24,506 --> 00:58:26,633
They couldn't find anything at all.

857
00:58:26,716 --> 00:58:29,135
They did a thorough check
from his consultation fee

858
00:58:29,219 --> 00:58:31,429
to the litigation expenses
and found nothing.

859
00:58:32,055 --> 00:58:35,266
I checked his card details and account,
and he surprisingly doesn't spend much.

860
00:58:35,350 --> 00:58:37,477
He just often goes to the car wash.

861
00:58:37,560 --> 00:58:39,562
- But…
- But what?

862
00:58:39,646 --> 00:58:42,649
He'd withdraw millions in cash
every now and then.

863
00:58:43,399 --> 00:58:44,399
- Is that so?
- Yes.

864
00:58:45,360 --> 00:58:47,946
Another odd thing is that
he'd always spend 300,000 won

865
00:58:48,029 --> 00:58:51,115
at Moulin Rouge
on the day of his withdrawal.

866
00:58:51,741 --> 00:58:53,535
Moulin Rouge?

867
00:58:54,410 --> 00:58:55,954
- A bar?
- A flower shop.

868
00:59:13,179 --> 00:59:16,849
He spent 300,000 won today
and sent the flowers to a Kim Min-ji.

869
00:59:16,933 --> 00:59:18,768
That's a female name.

870
00:59:19,644 --> 00:59:21,187
- I believe so.
- I see.

871
00:59:22,105 --> 00:59:25,149
So he bought some flowers
and withdrew some cash

872
00:59:25,233 --> 00:59:27,360
before meeting this Kim Min-ji?

873
00:59:29,362 --> 00:59:30,362
Where?

874
00:59:30,989 --> 00:59:32,949
Where is she right now?

875
00:59:35,368 --> 00:59:36,995
KIM MIN-JI
GANGJU-GU, SEOUL

876
00:59:37,078 --> 00:59:38,621
DAUGHTERS
KIM MIN-JI

877
00:59:38,705 --> 00:59:41,749
CEO HONG HAE-IN OF QUEENS DEPARTMENT STORE

878
00:59:47,005 --> 00:59:48,047
Ms. Hong.

879
00:59:52,010 --> 00:59:53,094
Ms. Hong.

880
00:59:54,178 --> 00:59:55,305
Ms. Kim Min-ji?

881
00:59:56,097 --> 00:59:58,099
Deal with our customers only.

882
01:00:01,853 --> 01:00:04,063
The company already helped
with the funeral.

883
01:00:04,147 --> 01:00:08,401
You personally sent us flowers
and gave us a lot of condolence money.

884
01:00:08,484 --> 01:00:10,236
And you even made time to visit.

885
01:00:10,737 --> 01:00:12,739
I don't know how to thank…

886
01:00:49,776 --> 01:00:54,238
I guess Mr. Baek has been sending
condolence flowers under your name.

887
01:00:55,782 --> 01:00:57,575
I'm a bit touched.

888
01:01:01,329 --> 01:01:02,329
I like it.

889
01:01:03,164 --> 01:01:04,207
Like what?

890
01:01:04,791 --> 01:01:06,417
All funeral halls are the same.

891
01:01:06,501 --> 01:01:09,128
But this place is clean and modern.

892
01:01:09,837 --> 01:01:13,007
There aren't just chrysanthemums,
but dahlias and tulips as well.

893
01:01:13,091 --> 01:01:14,801
It brightens up the room.

894
01:01:15,677 --> 01:01:16,844
Are those angels?

895
01:01:17,637 --> 01:01:19,722
Rococo style. I like it.

896
01:01:20,598 --> 01:01:23,434
I also like how they
have halogen lamps here,

897
01:01:23,518 --> 01:01:25,853
but pin lights over her photo.

898
01:01:27,563 --> 01:01:30,316
Are you looking for a funeral hall?

899
01:01:32,944 --> 01:01:33,944
What?

900
01:01:34,237 --> 01:01:36,656
I mean, you're looking around so closely.

901
01:01:39,325 --> 01:01:40,660
I was just looking around.

902
01:01:41,661 --> 01:01:42,662
I see.

903
01:01:43,538 --> 01:01:46,958
It's been a while
since we came to a funeral like this one.

904
01:01:48,126 --> 01:01:50,336
Most of the funerals we go to

905
01:01:51,254 --> 01:01:53,673
rarely have family members
weeping like them.

906
01:01:57,051 --> 01:02:00,012
They're busy consulting
their attorneys or accountants

907
01:02:00,096 --> 01:02:02,140
about their inheritance or gift tax.

908
01:02:04,642 --> 01:02:06,144
Mom…

909
01:02:06,811 --> 01:02:07,854
You're right.

910
01:02:09,731 --> 01:02:12,984
They're genuinely mourning.

911
01:02:37,008 --> 01:02:38,551
Why did you send flowers?

912
01:02:39,343 --> 01:02:40,887
And the condolence money?

913
01:02:42,972 --> 01:02:44,974
Stop playing. You disgust me.

914
01:02:45,641 --> 01:02:49,103
Even if I lose my memory down the road,

915
01:02:49,187 --> 01:02:51,355
I will never forget what you did to me.

916
01:02:52,023 --> 01:02:54,525
You let go of my hand when I was

917
01:02:55,401 --> 01:02:56,401
the most helpless.

918
01:02:59,197 --> 01:03:02,074
I will never forgive you.

919
01:03:02,158 --> 01:03:04,911
Try all you want,

920
01:03:06,662 --> 01:03:08,831
but I will resent you
until my last breath.

921
01:03:09,916 --> 01:03:12,794
So all you need to do

922
01:03:13,753 --> 01:03:15,171
is stay still…

923
01:03:17,507 --> 01:03:19,675
and get lost when I tell you to.

924
01:03:41,113 --> 01:03:42,907
- That was quick.
- Of course, it was.

925
01:03:47,870 --> 01:03:49,997
- What is it?
- It's nothing.

926
01:03:50,581 --> 01:03:53,835
- I don't want to add fuel to the fire.
- No, let me hear it.

927
01:03:54,919 --> 01:03:55,919
What is it?

928
01:03:56,504 --> 01:03:59,215
Did you know that Secretary Kim
and I have become quite close?

929
01:03:59,298 --> 01:04:00,383
We just spoke on the phone.

930
01:04:00,466 --> 01:04:03,010
"How are they doing?
Do you think they reconciled?

931
01:04:03,094 --> 01:04:05,888
Where are they going after work?
Don't let them cross paths."

932
01:04:05,972 --> 01:04:08,474
- That's what secretaries...
- It's not just us.

933
01:04:08,975 --> 01:04:10,768
All the workers are dying too.

934
01:04:10,852 --> 01:04:12,895
They liked it better when you didn't care.

935
01:04:13,813 --> 01:04:15,982
But you've been having
good and bad days lately.

936
01:04:16,065 --> 01:04:18,526
Enough. It's best that I don't hear it.

937
01:04:19,652 --> 01:04:20,987
You made me talk.

938
01:04:21,487 --> 01:04:24,073
Anyway, there's one thing
you can do for us.

939
01:04:24,156 --> 01:04:25,783
- Remaining amicable.
- Enough.

940
01:04:25,867 --> 01:04:27,535
It'd be best if you went on a trip.

941
01:04:27,618 --> 01:04:29,620
- Abroad if possible.
- Aren't you busy?

942
01:04:30,162 --> 01:04:32,123
Of course, I am. I'm your secretary.

943
01:04:33,541 --> 01:04:35,251
You're having dinner with Mr. Yoon.

944
01:04:36,294 --> 01:04:37,545
You're seeing him often.

945
01:04:41,007 --> 01:04:42,007
Isn't it great?

946
01:04:42,800 --> 01:04:44,385
No split levels.

947
01:04:44,468 --> 01:04:48,556
An entry fee of 8% is not bad.

948
01:04:49,223 --> 01:04:53,311
But why does he want Hercyna
to hire their own employees?

949
01:04:53,394 --> 01:04:54,520
That's his rule.

950
01:04:54,604 --> 01:04:57,523
- The workers need to be 27 or younger.
- I know, but why?

951
01:04:58,524 --> 01:05:01,152
He doesn't want old employees
to sell his products.

952
01:05:03,321 --> 01:05:04,363
Unbelievable.

953
01:05:04,447 --> 01:05:07,533
What's so terrible about aging?
It's actually a blessing.

954
01:05:07,617 --> 01:05:09,619
It's great and something to vie for.

955
01:05:09,702 --> 01:05:11,037
It's beautiful.

956
01:05:14,498 --> 01:05:15,498
He's obnoxious.

957
01:05:17,501 --> 01:05:21,088
So will you give up then?
He accepted almost all of our conditions.

958
01:05:21,631 --> 01:05:22,632
"Our"?

959
01:05:30,222 --> 01:05:31,515
Your conditions.

960
01:05:32,808 --> 01:05:35,311
Yes, he accepted my conditions

961
01:05:35,394 --> 01:05:38,272
for your sake.

962
01:05:38,356 --> 01:05:39,440
So tell me.

963
01:05:42,443 --> 01:05:43,444
What do you want?

964
01:05:44,654 --> 01:05:46,906
I know I owe you one.

965
01:05:47,990 --> 01:05:50,701
I feel uneasy
since you're not asking me for a favor.

966
01:05:51,494 --> 01:05:54,538
If it's something I can do right now,
then I'll do it.

967
01:05:57,416 --> 01:05:59,293
- Divorce him.
- What?

968
01:06:02,213 --> 01:06:03,798
Divorce Baek Hyun-woo.

969
01:06:05,216 --> 01:06:06,634
That's what I want.

970
01:06:10,346 --> 01:06:13,182
He was planning to leave you.
Will you still keep him?

971
01:06:24,610 --> 01:06:25,610
That's my business.

972
01:06:27,029 --> 01:06:29,407
You're crossing the line again.

973
01:06:32,743 --> 01:06:34,662
Should I really cross the line this time?

974
01:06:36,455 --> 01:06:37,665
What if I…

975
01:06:41,043 --> 01:06:42,043
replaced him?

976
01:06:57,351 --> 01:07:00,563
I'd be crossing the line
if I really asked you that.

977
01:07:23,169 --> 01:07:24,170
I can't eat.

978
01:07:25,963 --> 01:07:29,550
I can't digest food well
when I'm offended.

979
01:08:07,963 --> 01:08:10,341
He was adopted by a Korean family at 12.

980
01:08:10,424 --> 01:08:12,718
The US may be vast,
but the Korean community is small.

981
01:08:12,802 --> 01:08:17,098
Our new international attorney
used to live in his neighborhood.

982
01:08:17,181 --> 01:08:19,892
They weren't close,
but his family was well-known.

983
01:08:19,975 --> 01:08:22,061
- How so?
- It was soon after he was adopted.

984
01:08:22,144 --> 01:08:24,063
His adoptive parents moved
to a bigger house.

985
01:08:24,146 --> 01:08:26,690
Then they sent him
to the most expensive private school.

986
01:08:26,774 --> 01:08:28,400
Hill Crawford Academy.

987
01:08:29,068 --> 01:08:31,278
The annual tuition costs over $60,000.

988
01:08:31,362 --> 01:08:33,197
But his parents weren't rich.

989
01:08:33,280 --> 01:08:35,199
Can you reach his parents?

990
01:08:35,282 --> 01:08:36,282
I did look into it.

991
01:08:37,368 --> 01:08:38,994
They both passed away.

992
01:08:39,078 --> 01:08:41,038
It was a drunk driving accident.

993
01:08:41,122 --> 01:08:43,457
But people thought it was odd

994
01:08:44,416 --> 01:08:46,335
since neither of them were drinkers.

995
01:09:32,006 --> 01:09:33,132
You shouldn't be here.

996
01:09:34,925 --> 01:09:37,928
How is this place?
It was empty for a long time.

997
01:09:38,721 --> 01:09:39,722
You should go.

998
01:09:39,805 --> 01:09:43,559
I feel reassured to know that my son
is living under the same roof as me.

999
01:09:45,603 --> 01:09:46,604
I told you to leave.

1000
01:09:48,314 --> 01:09:52,234
- You need to be more careful, Ms. Moh.
- Don't call me that. Call me Mom.

1001
01:09:54,111 --> 01:09:57,406
You told me not to call you that,
so I held myself back all along.

1002
01:09:58,199 --> 01:09:59,700
Now, I can't even say it anymore.

1003
01:10:01,160 --> 01:10:02,369
Right.

1004
01:10:04,413 --> 01:10:06,749
We had quite a past.

1005
01:10:10,044 --> 01:10:11,754
But I don't regret it.

1006
01:10:13,881 --> 01:10:16,383
Really? When this is your life right now?

1007
01:10:17,885 --> 01:10:20,054
She's a housekeeper.

1008
01:10:20,137 --> 01:10:21,597
She's been here for a while.

1009
01:10:21,680 --> 01:10:23,098
You could say she's like

1010
01:10:23,182 --> 01:10:25,643
the head housekeeper
whom Grandfather relies on.

1011
01:10:25,726 --> 01:10:26,769
Don't mind her.

1012
01:10:26,852 --> 01:10:27,852
She's a nobody.

1013
01:10:28,312 --> 01:10:29,688
And over there…

1014
01:10:34,902 --> 01:10:35,903
Gosh, that's salty.

1015
01:10:35,986 --> 01:10:37,571
Ms. Moh has lost her touch.

1016
01:10:37,655 --> 01:10:40,115
Why is this so salty?

1017
01:10:40,199 --> 01:10:43,202
That's why
you should kick her out this instant.

1018
01:10:43,285 --> 01:10:46,413
I would've done that already
if it was up to me.

1019
01:10:47,039 --> 01:10:49,583
- Eat up. The other dishes are fine.
- Okay.

1020
01:10:53,254 --> 01:10:56,215
Don't you remember everything you've lost
in the past 30 years?

1021
01:10:58,384 --> 01:10:59,551
Of course, I do.

1022
01:10:59,635 --> 01:11:01,679
I wanted to keep my son close

1023
01:11:02,304 --> 01:11:04,139
and raise him myself.

1024
01:11:04,223 --> 01:11:08,060
But if I did, you wouldn't
have gotten nice birthday meals

1025
01:11:08,143 --> 01:11:11,021
or brand-new school uniforms.

1026
01:11:11,105 --> 01:11:12,606
We would've been dirt-poor.

1027
01:11:12,690 --> 01:11:15,192
I would've said,
"We're a family. Hang in there."

1028
01:11:15,276 --> 01:11:16,944
"Things will look up soon."

1029
01:11:17,569 --> 01:11:21,073
But that wouldn't have happened.

1030
01:11:24,910 --> 01:11:26,370
It's a nice house, isn't it?

1031
01:11:27,663 --> 01:11:29,707
Chairman Hong is very meticulous.

1032
01:11:30,416 --> 01:11:32,584
It took him five years
to build this house,

1033
01:11:32,668 --> 01:11:34,628
when it would've taken others one year.

1034
01:11:34,712 --> 01:11:38,173
He even chose which stones
to put in the garden.

1035
01:11:40,843 --> 01:11:43,512
But soon,

1036
01:11:43,595 --> 01:11:45,889
we'll kick them all out

1037
01:11:45,973 --> 01:11:47,725
and have this house to ourselves.

1038
01:11:50,811 --> 01:11:52,438
Don't think it's unfair.

1039
01:11:53,147 --> 01:11:56,942
We're just changing the order of things.

1040
01:11:57,026 --> 01:11:59,570
This family had everything
they ever wanted.

1041
01:11:59,653 --> 01:12:00,988
They were happy.

1042
01:12:01,071 --> 01:12:02,071
And now,

1043
01:12:02,698 --> 01:12:04,450
we will take over

1044
01:12:05,993 --> 01:12:06,993
and become happy.

1045
01:12:09,747 --> 01:12:11,623
You're more careless than I thought.

1046
01:12:12,541 --> 01:12:13,751
Do you think it'll be easy?

1047
01:12:15,085 --> 01:12:17,171
- I...
- No, there it goes.

1048
01:12:17,254 --> 01:12:18,464
Kick the ball to me.

1049
01:12:18,547 --> 01:12:19,923
I want to do it too.

1050
01:12:20,007 --> 01:12:21,508
It's over there.

1051
01:12:21,592 --> 01:12:23,052
Guys, have a drink.

1052
01:12:23,135 --> 01:12:25,012
Mommy brought drinks.

1053
01:12:25,095 --> 01:12:27,723
- Let's go.
- Can we have it now?

1054
01:12:27,806 --> 01:12:28,891
Can we really drink it?

1055
01:12:28,974 --> 01:12:30,392
Come here!

1056
01:12:35,064 --> 01:12:37,232
Goodness, my princess.

1057
01:12:37,316 --> 01:12:38,776
Are you up?

1058
01:12:39,651 --> 01:12:42,905
Goodness, you're so pretty.

1059
01:12:44,531 --> 01:12:46,700
Goodness.

1060
01:12:47,451 --> 01:12:49,286
Beom-jun, be careful.

1061
01:12:49,370 --> 01:12:51,747
Guys, look here.

1062
01:12:51,830 --> 01:12:53,457
- Carry me.
- Sure.

1063
01:12:53,540 --> 01:12:55,667
Chairman Hong enjoyed
his happiness before us,

1064
01:12:55,751 --> 01:12:57,544
and he still remembers those times.

1065
01:12:57,628 --> 01:12:59,296
We've yet to take them away.

1066
01:12:59,380 --> 01:13:00,297
You won't fall.

1067
01:13:00,381 --> 01:13:01,507
We shouldn't be

1068
01:13:02,800 --> 01:13:04,218
complacent like this.

1069
01:13:15,562 --> 01:13:18,190
- What is this?
- Use it however you want.

1070
01:13:19,566 --> 01:13:21,568
Where can I possibly use this?

1071
01:13:22,694 --> 01:13:26,281
Secretary Jang told me that you'll
be investigated for the secret fund.

1072
01:13:26,990 --> 01:13:29,535
Your son or grandson
can't go to prison for you

1073
01:13:29,618 --> 01:13:31,745
since they have a lot on their plate.

1074
01:13:32,246 --> 01:13:33,997
- So?
- I'll go instead.

1075
01:13:35,416 --> 01:13:38,460
Let's say I secretly embezzled
your secret fund

1076
01:13:38,544 --> 01:13:40,379
through the scholarship foundation.

1077
01:13:41,296 --> 01:13:45,259
I'm neither a board member
nor your family by law.

1078
01:13:45,342 --> 01:13:49,471
If I take responsibility, you won't have
to worry about the owner's risk.

1079
01:13:50,097 --> 01:13:53,392
Even if the media covers it,
I can take the fall alone.

1080
01:13:53,475 --> 01:13:55,853
There's no honor I need to keep,

1081
01:13:56,603 --> 01:13:57,603
so it's okay.

1082
01:13:58,272 --> 01:14:01,608
I'll be interrogated
and go to prison instead.

1083
01:14:02,734 --> 01:14:03,861
Don't you worry.

1084
01:14:13,162 --> 01:14:15,038
You're much better

1085
01:14:16,957 --> 01:14:18,834
than all my children combined.

1086
01:15:05,672 --> 01:15:06,757
Hae-in.

1087
01:15:12,054 --> 01:15:15,015
Why are you out in the cold?
Where's your car?

1088
01:15:16,183 --> 01:15:18,393
Where is it? Where's Mr. Oh?

1089
01:15:34,660 --> 01:15:35,786
I'm not sure.

1090
01:15:38,163 --> 01:15:39,790
How did I get here?

1091
01:15:46,338 --> 01:15:48,131
I keep finding myself
like this these days.

1092
01:15:48,924 --> 01:15:52,052
Time keeps slipping away
when I'm running out of time as is.

1093
01:15:56,348 --> 01:15:57,599
What about you?

1094
01:15:58,141 --> 01:15:59,560
How did you know I was here?

1095
01:16:05,148 --> 01:16:07,317
Did you recognize this umbrella?

1096
01:16:08,652 --> 01:16:10,529
Do you remember giving it to me?

1097
01:16:12,072 --> 01:16:14,741
I was really dumbfounded back then.

1098
01:16:17,286 --> 01:16:18,286
Hae-in.

1099
01:16:20,539 --> 01:16:22,541
Don't give me that look.

1100
01:16:22,624 --> 01:16:24,334
There's a 51% chance.

1101
01:16:24,418 --> 01:16:26,670
I can go to Germany and receive treatment.

1102
01:16:39,141 --> 01:16:40,142
Hae-in.

1103
01:16:40,225 --> 01:16:41,602
Why do you keep calling me?

1104
01:17:09,212 --> 01:17:13,800
Right. You know Ye-na, right?
She got into a car accident two days ago.

1105
01:17:13,884 --> 01:17:18,764
She fainted and went to the ER.

1106
01:17:19,348 --> 01:17:20,641
Then, her husband…

1107
01:17:21,266 --> 01:17:24,061
Then, her husband
and her attorney rushed over.

1108
01:17:24,144 --> 01:17:28,565
He caused a scene
and said she had to revise her will.

1109
01:17:28,649 --> 01:17:32,152
He was so noisy that she woke up.

1110
01:17:42,454 --> 01:17:43,747
Are you crying?

1111
01:17:47,417 --> 01:17:48,752
I'm sorry.

1112
01:17:51,588 --> 01:17:53,006
About what?

1113
01:18:01,932 --> 01:18:03,100
Are you that worried?

1114
01:18:08,897 --> 01:18:10,232
Don't you worry.

1115
01:18:25,831 --> 01:18:26,831
Baek Hyun-woo.

1116
01:18:29,793 --> 01:18:30,793
I love you.

1117
01:19:21,845 --> 01:19:24,055
- Her name is Yeong-suk.
- Forget it.

1118
01:19:24,139 --> 01:19:26,349
- I recognize that name.
- Yes, ma'am.

1119
01:19:32,022 --> 01:19:33,857
That was ages ago.

1120
01:19:35,442 --> 01:19:37,110
He's still calling for her?

1121
01:19:37,194 --> 01:19:40,655
QUEENS DEPARTMENT STORE
GUIDE MAP

1122
01:19:41,406 --> 01:19:43,200
Mr. Baek, did you know?

1123
01:19:43,283 --> 01:19:45,994
A raccoon lives on our rooftop garden.

1124
01:19:46,077 --> 01:19:48,079
That can't be.

1125
01:19:48,163 --> 01:19:50,332
There are no raccoons in Seoul.

1126
01:19:50,415 --> 01:19:51,415
I saw her.

1127
01:19:52,334 --> 01:19:53,460
Many times.

1128
01:19:54,085 --> 01:19:55,462
- Really?
- Yes.

1129
01:19:56,087 --> 01:19:59,174
She only comes out of hiding
when it's empty and you call her name.

1130
01:20:01,802 --> 01:20:03,136
She comes out?

1131
01:20:06,515 --> 01:20:07,808
That's impossible.

1132
01:20:08,683 --> 01:20:10,977
You must take me for a fool.

1133
01:20:11,978 --> 01:20:12,979
I'm serious.

1134
01:20:15,148 --> 01:20:16,650
Her name is Yeong-suk.

1135
01:20:22,072 --> 01:20:23,198
You're lying, aren't you?

1136
01:20:23,824 --> 01:20:26,159
Call out her name when no one's around.

1137
01:20:26,243 --> 01:20:29,204
But she only comes out when she wants to.

1138
01:20:36,545 --> 01:20:38,630
Come on. Don't lie.

1139
01:20:40,131 --> 01:20:41,299
You're lying.

1140
01:20:42,050 --> 01:20:43,718
She's so adorable.

1141
01:20:51,393 --> 01:20:53,019
You're fooling me again.

1142
01:20:54,396 --> 01:20:55,522
You're lying.

1143
01:20:56,273 --> 01:20:57,524
She has big, round eyes.

1144
01:20:58,358 --> 01:20:59,568
I know you'll love her too.

1145
01:21:08,827 --> 01:21:10,954
I'm sorry, but you're not fooling me.

1146
01:21:11,580 --> 01:21:14,875
He is a fool. He still believes it.

1147
01:21:16,251 --> 01:21:18,587
Does he believe everything I say?

1148
01:21:25,135 --> 01:21:29,097
No wonder he married me after I said

1149
01:21:31,057 --> 01:21:32,517
I'd make him happy.

1150
01:21:38,940 --> 01:21:39,940
Yeong-suk.

1151
01:21:40,859 --> 01:21:42,652
Come out if you're here.

1152
01:21:44,738 --> 01:21:45,864
Yeong-suk?

1153
01:22:02,422 --> 01:22:04,257
Yeong-suk!

1154
01:22:11,348 --> 01:22:13,433
I want to see you, Yeong-suk.

1155
01:22:17,520 --> 01:22:20,357
QUEEN OF TEARS

1156
01:22:51,721 --> 01:22:54,140
He ran laps, and had rice soup again.

1157
01:22:54,224 --> 01:22:55,600
Is this fun?

1158
01:22:56,851 --> 01:22:58,478
How could I possibly leave her?

1159
01:22:58,561 --> 01:22:59,561
Get out.

1160
01:23:00,563 --> 01:23:02,607
A reunion? A bar? There's only one answer.

1161
01:23:02,691 --> 01:23:04,067
A mistress.

1162
01:23:05,485 --> 01:23:07,696
Why are you still here
and letting them humiliate you?

1163
01:23:08,363 --> 01:23:09,489
That today will be

1164
01:23:09,572 --> 01:23:12,409
the best day of my life.

1165
01:23:12,492 --> 01:23:14,577
She'll choose me anyway.

1166
01:23:15,120 --> 01:23:16,371
You! Let her go!

1167
01:23:16,830 --> 01:23:18,456
And if you try to harm her,

1168
01:23:18,540 --> 01:23:20,250
I'll do the same to you.

1169
01:23:26,840 --> 01:23:28,842
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim
